- The integer array parameter `people` must not be null.
- The integer array parameter `people` must have a length greater than or equal to 1 and less than or equal to 2000.
- Each element in the integer array parameter `people` must be an array of length 2.
- The first element of each sub-array in the integer array parameter `people` must be greater than or equal to 0 and less than or equal to 10^6.
- The second element of each sub-array in the integer array parameter `people` must be greater than or equal to 0 and less than the length of the integer array parameter `people`.
- The reconstructed queue returned as an integer array must have the same length as the input `people` array.
- The reconstructed queue must be ordered based on the height and number of people in front as specified in the input `people` array.